name: Hubble mosaic of the majestic Sombrero Galaxy
description:
The Sombrero lies at the southern edge of the rich Virgo cluster of galaxies and is one of the most massive objects in that group, equivalent to 800 billion suns. The galaxy is 50,000 light-years across and is located 30 million light-years from Earth.

Name:	M 104, Sombrero Galaxy
Type:	Local Universe : Galaxy : Type : Spiral
Distance:	30 million light years
Constellation:	Virgo
Category:	Galaxies

3,629 editions for the known 3,629 planetary systems to date.
